1
00:00:01,070 --> 00:00:03,610
(Episode 68)

2
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:06,280
What?

3
00:00:09,880 --> 00:00:10,920
Oh my!

4
00:00:12,250 --> 00:00:16,390
What are you doing? You startled me.
What if our coworkers see us?

5
00:00:16,450 --> 00:00:20,560
Isn't this the thrill of office romance?
Sneaking around behind our coworkers.

6
00:00:20,690 --> 00:00:22,630
You're nuts. You're really nuts.

7
00:00:23,090 --> 00:00:26,060
I'm just so happy I get to work
on this with you, Jang Mi.

8
00:00:27,030 --> 00:00:30,500
Me too. But I feel bad, Baek Ho.

9
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:33,170
I'm worried I'm making things harder
for you for no reason.

10
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:34,540
Why would you feel bad, Jang Mi?

11
00:00:34,870 --> 00:00:37,840
I want to find out how my dad really got
into that car accident,

12
00:00:37,910 --> 00:00:40,550
- so I wanted to do this with you.
- Even so...

13
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:48,850
- Gosh, seriously.
- I'll go wait in Jun Ho's office.

14
00:00:49,290 --> 00:00:50,720
- See you later.
- Okay.

15
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:53,930
What?

16
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:56,560
Oh my!

17
00:01:00,770 --> 00:01:01,770
Gosh.

18
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:06,940
General Manager Kang...

19
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:11,740
Hwa Young. There you are.

20
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:14,810
Professor, what brings you here so early?

21
00:01:14,910 --> 00:01:18,620
I came to meet Jun Ho early
to talk about the project's progress.

22
00:01:19,450 --> 00:01:20,550
I see.

23
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:22,990
General Manager Kang will be here
any minute.

24
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:24,960
- You should wait and see him.
- Hwa Young.

25
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:27,160
We need to talk.

26
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:31,160
- Let's talk later. We're at the office.
- Hwa Young.

27
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:34,200
Do we really have to make
our Jun Ho and Director Ma...

28
00:01:34,870 --> 00:01:36,630
get married?

29
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,940
- Yes.
- Why? Why do we have to do that?

30
00:01:40,140 --> 00:01:43,410
I've told you already.
My Seo Rin likes General Manager Kang.

31
00:01:43,980 --> 00:01:48,080
How many times do I have to tell you that
as her mother, I'm making this happen?

32
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:50,680
It's just that I find it hard to accept.

33
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:54,190
From what I can tell, it's not like
they're madly in love with each other.

34
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:58,790
- Why do you insist on this alone?
- Professor.

35
00:01:58,860 --> 00:02:03,260
Even if they do like each other,
our love comes first.

36
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:05,760
Hwa Young, just tell me.

37
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:09,000
You do love me, don't you?

38
00:02:09,730 --> 00:02:13,370
What's the point of bringing that up now?

39
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:18,210
We must put our love aside for the kids.
That's the adult thing to do.

40
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:20,780
You need to accept reality, Professor.

41
00:02:21,350 --> 00:02:22,580
We're over.

42
00:02:24,450 --> 00:02:25,450
What do you mean, "over?"

43
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:29,550
Hwa Young, are you really saying
that your feelings for me are gone?

44
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:33,090
Professor, let's talk about this later.

45
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:39,530
I can never be over you, Hwa Young.
Just because you say we're over,

46
00:02:39,830 --> 00:02:43,470
- that doesn't mean we are.
- Professor, please don't be like this.

47
00:02:44,340 --> 00:02:46,600
We're about to become in-laws.

48
00:02:49,940 --> 00:02:52,080
(General Manager's Office)

49
00:02:54,210 --> 00:02:55,210
Jun Ho.

50
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:08,290
Dad?

51
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:23,410
What did I just see?

52
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:28,080
Tell me what's going on.

53
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,550
Don't tell me all this time...

54
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,950
Have you been having an affair
with CEO Chae?

55
00:03:34,690 --> 00:03:35,820
Betraying Mom?

56
00:03:39,460 --> 00:03:43,390
Oh my gosh, what a coincidence
running into you again.

57
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:46,830
I know, right? It's unbelievable.

58
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:49,900
It really feels like fate
between us, Hong Ju.

59
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,800
Really?

60
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:54,940
Fate. I like the sound of that.

61
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:57,980
Destined to be mother-in-law
and daughter-in-law!

62
00:04:00,950 --> 00:04:02,310
I love that.

63
00:04:02,910 --> 00:04:07,190
You only bought things for the Professor?
You didn't get anything for yourself.

64
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:11,660
This is a gift for you.

65
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,520
What's this?

66
00:04:13,690 --> 00:04:15,930
I saw it and thought it would look
great on you, so I bought it.

67
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:18,500
You shouldn't have.
You keep buying me gifts.

68
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,170
Oh my!

69
00:04:21,770 --> 00:04:25,100
It's beautiful. Wow, you have great taste.

70
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:29,470
You're such an amazing wife to him.

71
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:34,950
If I marry Baek Ho, I want to be like you
and take great care of him.

72
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:37,880
Yes. That would be wonderful.

73
00:04:41,590 --> 00:04:44,060
What am I going to do?
Baek Ho saw everything.

74
00:04:49,890 --> 00:04:50,900
CEO Chae.

75
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:52,760
Is something the matter?

76
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:57,540
- Manager Lee.
- With Professor Kang...

77
00:04:58,500 --> 00:04:59,940
Did something happen?

78
00:05:01,110 --> 00:05:02,770
You need to tell me what's going on
so I can handle it.

79
00:05:03,110 --> 00:05:04,580
Me, being with Professor Kang...

80
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:08,510
- Did General Manager Kang catch you?
- No!

81
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:11,620
There is no way Jun Ho can find out.

82
00:05:12,420 --> 00:05:13,420
Then who?

83
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:17,290
The Lawyer Kang Baek Ho saw us.
He saw everything. What do I do?

84
00:05:18,660 --> 00:05:23,230
What if Jun Ho and Seo Rin's wedding
gets called off because of this?

85
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:26,600
This is exactly why I told you
to stop seeing Professor Kang.

86
00:05:27,030 --> 00:05:29,170
- Do you like Professor Kang that much?
- Lee Kang Hyuk!

87
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:33,570
- Are you trying to add fuel to the fire?
- You're in no position to yell at me.

88
00:05:35,470 --> 00:05:36,910
Now that Kang Baek Ho knows,

89
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:39,910
he'll instantly realize
that his father was being used,

90
00:05:40,010 --> 00:05:43,510
and if that happens, Professor Kang
will also start to think...

91
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:46,780
that he was a victim
in Oh Bok Gil's car accident.

92
00:05:47,020 --> 00:05:49,520
Can you handle all of that?

93
00:05:50,090 --> 00:05:52,260
That's why I'm panicking! That's why!

94
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:54,090
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

95
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,930
How long have you and CEO Chae...

96
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:02,930
been seeing each other like this?

97
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:06,870
Does Mom know? Of course not.

98
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:08,810
Mom wouldn't have the slightest clue.

99
00:06:10,140 --> 00:06:11,140
It's not like that.

100
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:13,510
It's not what you think.

101
00:06:13,580 --> 00:06:15,410
What do you mean it's not?
I saw you with my own two eyes.

102
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:17,750
I'm so disappointed in you, Dad.

103
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:21,090
- I can't believe this is who you are.
- What do you know about any of this?

104
00:06:21,990 --> 00:06:23,520
This is grown-up business. Stay out of it.

105
00:06:23,590 --> 00:06:26,560
You can't just brush this off
and expect it to go away.

106
00:06:27,330 --> 00:06:30,760
Back when you came to the cafe
where Tae Pyung used to sing,

107
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,160
that's when it started, wasn't it?

108
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,970
Hey, I told you to knock it off.

109
00:06:36,470 --> 00:06:40,570
In the past,
I admit I was tempted for a moment,

110
00:06:41,870 --> 00:06:44,910
- but I'm ending things now.
- And you call that an excuse?

111
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:48,280
Cheating on your partner.

112
00:06:48,580 --> 00:06:51,150
Don't you know how it destroys
a person's soul, Dad?

113
00:06:52,780 --> 00:06:56,820
How could you, after all she's done?
How could you do this to her?

114
00:06:57,090 --> 00:06:58,090
Baek Ho.

115
00:07:00,090 --> 00:07:01,830
All this time,

116
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:04,700
I've been wondering
why you had that car accident,

117
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:06,500
turning it over and over in my head,

118
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,470
and I was racking my brain
trying to figure it out.

119
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:11,070
So this is why.

120
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:13,910
What does the car accident
have to do with this?

121
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,310
Hey, what?

122
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:27,490
What? Why bring up that accident
out of nowhere?

123
00:07:27,690 --> 00:07:29,720
Dad, you were used by CEO Chae.

124
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,260
Can't you see that?

125
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:34,460
What? Me, being used?

126
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:37,600
CEO Chae is the one
who injured Jang Mi's father.

127
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,100
Here, in this hotel's
underground parking garage.

128
00:07:41,530 --> 00:07:43,400
Then, to cover up her crime,

129
00:07:43,970 --> 00:07:46,070
she put Jang Mi's unconscious father
in her car...

130
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:49,010
and abandoned him on the road
at the accident scene.

131
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:51,210
Then she must have called you.

132
00:07:51,810 --> 00:07:53,810
You left after getting a call
from CEO Chae, didn't you?

133
00:07:54,450 --> 00:07:55,450
Isn't that right?

134
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:00,650
Now all the pieces are falling into place,

135
00:08:01,590 --> 00:08:03,390
knowing that you and CEO Chae
were having an affair.

136
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:05,860
Then CEO Chae...

137
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,760
must have tricked you
into driving down that road...

138
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:11,430
to set you up to hit
Jang Mi's father with your car.

139
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:12,500
Kang Baek Ho.

140
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:15,630
What kind of ridiculous theory
are you making up?

141
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:18,700
Look, I know you feel betrayed.

142
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:21,240
But even so, how can you
falsely accuse CEO Chae like that?

143
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:24,380
It's not a false accusation.
Dad, she's the one fooling you.

144
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:28,280
Think about it, okay?
Your reputation is on the line.

145
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:31,820
You've crossed the line
suspecting CEO Chae like this.

146
00:08:32,550 --> 00:08:35,820
I was planning on ending things
with her anyway.

147
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:39,490
So, if you really care about your mother,

148
00:08:40,790 --> 00:08:43,290
just pretend you
didn't see anything today.

149
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:45,730
And don't let on about this
to your brother.

150
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:47,630
Not let on about what?

151
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:54,370
What are you warning
Baek Ho not to tell me?

152
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:04,050
It's...

153
00:09:04,620 --> 00:09:05,720
Your mother's birthday.

154
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:07,550
Her birthday present, I mean.

155
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:12,090
Baek Ho's got the party bug again.

156
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,360
Baek Ho.

157
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:23,830
Yes, that should do it.

158
00:09:29,770 --> 00:09:30,780
Right.

159
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:32,710
That's all. You can go.

160
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:35,710
Have a seat, Lawyer Kang.

161
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:46,260
CEO Chae, I had no idea
you were so two-faced.

162
00:09:46,790 --> 00:09:49,390
One minute you're running away
after I caught you,

163
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:53,060
and the next you're sitting there
so elegantly as if nothing happened?

164
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:56,800
That facade is really something else.

165
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:59,940
Lawyer Kang, watch your mouth.

166
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,940
- I didn't run away.
- How long has this been going on?

167
00:10:03,770 --> 00:10:06,410
- What are you talking about?
- Toying with my father...

168
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:10,180
- and using him?
- Don't you know your father, Lawyer Kang?

169
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:15,420
Does your father seem like the type
to abandon his family for an affair?

170
00:10:16,290 --> 00:10:18,920
Your father and I are just friends.

171
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:22,960
A guy friend I can talk to comfortably.

172
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,960
You're the one who called my father...

173
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,000
and summoned him
to the accident scene, weren't you?

174
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:30,370
I have no idea what you're talking about.

175
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:34,270
I wondered why my father was
passing by there at that exact time.

176
00:10:35,940 --> 00:10:37,810
He was having an affair with you,

177
00:10:38,180 --> 00:10:41,680
so it makes perfect sense
that he'd come running at your call.

178
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:46,720
You used my father
under the guise of love.

179
00:10:47,050 --> 00:10:48,090
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

180
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:51,490
I'm only going to say this once,
so listen carefully.

181
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:53,890
Your father and I are...

182
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:57,230
around the same age
and occasionally have a drink,

183
00:10:57,630 --> 00:10:59,730
we're just comfortable
friends who can talk.

184
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:02,030
Nothing more, nothing less.

185
00:11:02,530 --> 00:11:04,240
And we are most certainly
not having an affair.

186
00:11:04,370 --> 00:11:09,040
Do friends hug each other so desperately
and profess their love?

187
00:11:10,070 --> 00:11:12,280
I saw you with my own two eyes.
Are you going to deny it?

188
00:11:12,410 --> 00:11:13,780
Kang Baek Ho, watch your tone.

189
00:11:14,810 --> 00:11:17,620
Where are you getting off
making up such ridiculous lies?

190
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:20,580
So this is how you always operate.

191
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:23,520
I'm finally seeing your true colors.

192
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:27,320
Since I saw it clearly
with my own two eyes,

193
00:11:28,660 --> 00:11:30,460
it's no use trying to deny it.

194
00:11:32,330 --> 00:11:34,030
If you spread any malicious rumors,

195
00:11:34,470 --> 00:11:36,770
I'll take everything
you've said to me today,

196
00:11:37,540 --> 00:11:39,770
and sue you for defamation.
So watch your mouth.

197
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,910
Threatening a lawyer with a lawsuit?

198
00:11:44,740 --> 00:11:46,040
I have to give you credit for your nerve.

199
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:47,980
But, CEO Chae Hwa Young,

200
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:50,410
you'd better be careful.

201
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:54,990
Because I will find the evidence
that you set my father up,

202
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,090
and I will bring you down.

203
00:11:58,820 --> 00:11:59,820
Kang Baek Ho!

204
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,870
Of all people, why did it have to be him?
This is going to be a problem.

205
00:12:14,370 --> 00:12:16,040
If he tells my dear Jun Ho,

206
00:12:16,870 --> 00:12:17,880
I'll be in big trouble.

207
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:25,050
I'm heading out for a delivery.

208
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:28,290
- Mom, I'm heading out now. Bye!
- Oh my!

209
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:31,660
I'm sorry.

210
00:12:42,670 --> 00:12:44,470
What an intoxicating scent!

211
00:12:44,670 --> 00:12:47,940
Oh my, I can hear bells
ringing in my heart.

212
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:52,440
I'm so sorry about that, ma'am.
Please, come on in.

213
00:12:58,050 --> 00:13:00,780
I had no idea
such a handsome man worked here.

214
00:13:01,490 --> 00:13:03,890
Wow, it's been so long since my heart
has raced like this.

215
00:13:06,990 --> 00:13:08,430
What can I get for you today?

216
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:15,170
That man who just left with the helmet is
one of your delivery guys, right?

217
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:18,040
Yes. May I ask why, ma'am?

218
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:23,110
I was just wondering
if you deliver to my area.

219
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:27,680
Do you live around here?
Then of course we can.

220
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:32,650
Just give us a call at this number,
and we'll deliver.

221
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:36,890
- Will the man from earlier be delivering?
- Excuse me?

222
00:13:38,490 --> 00:13:40,620
Actually, that's my younger brother.

223
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:47,570
My, you have such a handsome brother.

224
00:13:48,730 --> 00:13:53,240
- Pardon?
- I mean good looks run in the family.

225
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:58,540
You're too kind.
You're much lovelier, ma'am.

226
00:13:59,410 --> 00:14:00,410
Oh my.

227
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:06,580
Listen, actually, my place is
a little far from here,

228
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:08,120
so would you still be able to deliver?

229
00:14:08,190 --> 00:14:12,660
Of course. We deliver anywhere in Seoul,
so don't you worry.

230
00:14:14,090 --> 00:14:17,290
The helmet.
That guy's name was Oh Tae Pyung, right?

231
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:21,900
If Tae Pyung makes the delivery,
I'll get to see him again.

232
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:26,640
And if he meets Hwa Young,
I can see if he's the blackmailer.

233
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:30,170
Chae Hwa Young, just you wait.

234
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:34,550
Yes?

235
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:39,780
You haven't left for lunch yet.

236
00:14:40,250 --> 00:14:42,920
- What?
- Director Ma. Thank you for yesterday.

237
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:47,690
It was nothing. How's your hand?

238
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:51,800
It's fine. Things like this happened often
back when I was a chef.

239
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:52,900
It's nothing, really.

240
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:56,770
Seo Rin.

241
00:14:57,970 --> 00:15:00,400
Would you like to have lunch with me
at the hotel's Japanese restaurant?

242
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:02,140
I heard they have a new menu.

243
00:15:02,910 --> 00:15:06,380
I have somewhere I need to be.

244
00:15:07,110 --> 00:15:08,110
You're skipping lunch?

245
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:10,910
Yes, I'm meeting someone.

246
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:12,550
Please, excuse me.

247
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:15,290
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

248
00:15:17,790 --> 00:15:19,060
I wonder who she's meeting.

249
00:15:22,390 --> 00:15:26,330
How did you find out?
You must've been shocked, Baek Ho.

250
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:28,300
Jang Mi, did you know this whole time?

251
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:32,040
Then again, you live with CEO Chae,

252
00:15:32,370 --> 00:15:35,270
- so you must've known what was going on.
- I'm sorry, Baek Ho.

253
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:40,310
I didn't want to upset you
by bringing it up.

254
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:44,650
But that was shortsighted of me.
You had a right to know.

255
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:46,780
All this time,

256
00:15:47,020 --> 00:15:49,020
I wonder just how much
CEO Chae was using my dad.

257
00:15:49,220 --> 00:15:50,850
I feel awkward saying this,

258
00:15:51,790 --> 00:15:55,960
but it seems she used Professor Kang
for emotional support when she needed it.

259
00:15:56,590 --> 00:15:58,700
Team Leader Jin and her mother
have known for a while,

260
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:01,200
and I actually saw them together myself.

261
00:16:02,330 --> 00:16:03,370
I see.

262
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:08,270
I went to my brother's office earlier
and saw them too,

263
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:10,870
and I completely lost it.

264
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:16,580
Now that Chae Hwa Young knows
you're looking into my father's case,

265
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:19,380
- she'll be watching you more closely.
- I bet she will.

266
00:16:21,090 --> 00:16:23,890
I have a very clear picture
of what kind of person CEO Chae is now.

267
00:16:26,260 --> 00:16:27,590
My blood is boiling.

268
00:16:28,290 --> 00:16:30,530
My mom doted on my dad
and took such good care of him.

269
00:16:30,890 --> 00:16:32,060
How could he betray her like this?

270
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:34,570
It's not just your father's fault.

271
00:16:34,830 --> 00:16:39,100
Chae Hwa Young probably tricked him
and used him for her own personal gain.

272
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:49,110
So the person you had to meet was Baek Ho?

273
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:52,950
You should have just told me
you were meeting my brother.

274
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:58,360
I just asked to meet him briefly
for some personal legal advice.

275
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:01,760
I see.

276
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:05,330
Make sure you give her good advice.

277
00:17:10,470 --> 00:17:11,470
Yes, see you later.

278
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:23,250
Baek Ho and her,
are those two actually a thing?

279
00:17:28,050 --> 00:17:29,520
We're going to have to be careful.

280
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:31,020
Right?

281
00:17:31,420 --> 00:17:34,530
You could be in danger
with so many people watching, Jang Mi.

282
00:17:38,930 --> 00:17:41,100
Sounds like he's here.

283
00:17:44,670 --> 00:17:45,740
Delivery!

284
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:47,740
- Come on in.
- Thank you.

285
00:17:47,740 --> 00:17:49,710
Oh, my. Butterflies.

286
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:55,510
- Who is it?
- You know the side dishes Seo Rin loved?

287
00:17:55,710 --> 00:17:58,650
I ordered some from that same shop.

288
00:18:00,220 --> 00:18:03,390
Hey, Chairman Lee. It's me.

289
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:09,590
If I'd known you were a regular,
I would've thrown in some extras for you.

290
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:12,460
Wow, and so kind, too.

291
00:18:14,770 --> 00:18:17,300
Geum Soon. Ma'am.

292
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:20,600
Yes? What is it?

293
00:18:21,370 --> 00:18:24,880
You don't have to make side dishes today.
Mr. Tae Pyung here...

294
00:18:26,580 --> 00:18:27,910
You know my name?

295
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:32,180
Your sister mentioned it.

296
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:35,290
Mr. Tae Pyung must be thirsty
from his delivery.

297
00:18:35,290 --> 00:18:36,720
Please bring him some juice.

298
00:18:37,420 --> 00:18:39,920
- Yes, ma'am.
- Oh no, that's okay. I'm fine.

299
00:18:41,930 --> 00:18:45,160
But I won't feel right if you don't.

300
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:50,070
Your shop is a long way from here,
isn't it?

301
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:54,300
- This way, I won't feel as guilty.
- Right.

302
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:58,740
Is he possibly blackmailing Chae Hwa Young
for her money?

303
00:18:59,510 --> 00:19:02,110
But he really doesn't seem like the type.

304
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:07,920
If I just get my hands on her weakness,
it's game over.

305
00:19:08,790 --> 00:19:10,390
Thank you.

306
00:19:15,460 --> 00:19:17,490
The door's open. Is someone here?

307
00:19:22,830 --> 00:19:23,900
Oh Tae Pyung?

308
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:40,220
What?

309
00:19:40,580 --> 00:19:41,620
That's strange.

310
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:43,290
This is Tae Pyung's.

311
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:45,490
What's he doing here?

312
00:19:49,090 --> 00:19:51,530
What are you doing in my house,
Oh Tae Pyung?

313
00:19:52,930 --> 00:19:54,500
I'm here for a delivery.

314
00:19:54,930 --> 00:19:57,230
What? So they know each other?

315
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,500
Makes sense. You'd have to know her
to blackmail her.

316
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:03,240
A delivery? Who ordered it?

317
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:06,810
Why all the questions?
Who does she think I am? Her servant?

318
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,410
This is so frustrating.
Maybe I should just expose her.

319
00:20:09,650 --> 00:20:10,910
Why aren't you answering me?

320
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,780
I said, who ordered it?

321
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:17,320
I did. Why are you taking it out
on this poor young man?

322
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:21,260
- The madam ordered side dishes.
- A side dish delivery?

323
00:20:21,330 --> 00:20:22,330
Now, now.

324
00:20:22,590 --> 00:20:25,260
Why are you giving the delivery guy
such a hard time?

325
00:20:26,860 --> 00:20:29,200
Looks like you two know each other.

326
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,800
So how do you know our CEO Chae?

327
00:20:34,140 --> 00:20:35,140
Pardon?

328
00:20:40,410 --> 00:20:43,110
Should I tell them who you really are,
Chae Hwa Young?

329
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:45,780
- Should I?
- Yeom San Wol.

330
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:47,420
Did you set this all up?

331
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:50,820
What do you know, and why did you drag
Oh Tae Pyung into this?

332
00:20:53,620 --> 00:20:56,260
Then, I should get going.

333
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:06,870
Yeom San Wol. I need a word with you.

334
00:21:07,470 --> 00:21:08,470
Excuse me?

335
00:21:09,010 --> 00:21:11,710
Are you really calling your mother-in-law
by her name and glaring at me?

336
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:14,340
Why are you acting this way?
What did I do?

337
00:21:14,980 --> 00:21:17,510
All I did was order some marinated crab
for my darling husband...

338
00:21:17,950 --> 00:21:20,080
and some of his favorite kimchi.

339
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:21,720
I said,

340
00:21:22,390 --> 00:21:25,020
- I need a word with you.
- What do you two think you're doing?

341
00:21:25,460 --> 00:21:27,690
CEO Chae. We need to talk.

342
00:21:39,940 --> 00:21:42,170
Tae Pyung. Hey, Tae Pyung.

343
00:21:44,270 --> 00:21:45,280
Jang Mi?

344
00:21:47,080 --> 00:21:48,180
What happened in there?

345
00:21:48,380 --> 00:21:51,150
A woman named Yeom San Wol
placed the order.

346
00:21:51,350 --> 00:21:53,350
What? A delivery? All the way out here?

347
00:21:55,150 --> 00:21:57,290
- What's going on?
- I have no idea.

348
00:21:58,560 --> 00:22:01,660
But Chae Hwa Young seemed really rattled.

349
00:22:02,230 --> 00:22:04,330
I'll go inside and see
what I can find out.

350
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:07,500
- Get home safe.
- All right, Jang Mi.

351
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:20,410
Sweetheart, you're home?

352
00:22:25,950 --> 00:22:26,950
Mom.

353
00:22:27,450 --> 00:22:28,520
What is it, Baek Ho?

354
00:22:30,020 --> 00:22:32,290
Did something happen out there?

355
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:39,830
What's all this?

356
00:22:41,230 --> 00:22:43,000
And in front of your father, too.
How shameless.

357
00:22:43,670 --> 00:22:45,100
What has gotten into you?

358
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:46,800
Mom.

359
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,270
You know I love you, right?

360
00:22:50,110 --> 00:22:53,640
Oh, my. Hey, your father will get jealous.

361
00:22:54,410 --> 00:22:56,110
Move aside. Gosh.

362
00:22:56,950 --> 00:22:59,950
Seriously, you're still such a baby.

363
00:23:00,950 --> 00:23:03,820
All grown up, but still such a mama's boy.

364
00:23:12,530 --> 00:23:13,530
Baek Ho.

365
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:17,030
What's gotten into him?

366
00:23:22,910 --> 00:23:23,940
Chae Hwa Young.

367
00:23:24,570 --> 00:23:25,910
I'll never forgive her.

368
00:23:31,050 --> 00:23:34,680
(Dream Hotel)

369
00:23:39,020 --> 00:23:41,490
I need to find that USB
with all the evidence.

370
00:24:02,380 --> 00:24:03,650
Excuse me, CEO Chae.

371
00:24:04,450 --> 00:24:05,480
The thing is...

372
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,890
This isn't a designated parking spot.

373
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:11,450
Could you please move your car?

374
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:18,330
Do you not know who I am?

375
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:29,970
I saw the video.
We can really nail her with this.

376
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:33,310
- Let's send it to the news stations.
- I'll leak it to them anonymously.

377
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:37,610
But I'm worried CEO Chae will find a way
to wriggle out of this somehow.

378
00:24:37,710 --> 00:24:39,020
It won't be easy for her.

379
00:24:39,980 --> 00:24:42,920
We couldn't get footage of Dad's accident,
so this is the least we can do.

380
00:24:43,290 --> 00:24:45,160
Otherwise,
I won't be able to live with myself.

381
00:24:53,860 --> 00:24:55,670
(Dream Hotel CEO Chae Hwa Young's
abuse of power...)

382
00:24:58,770 --> 00:25:00,770
(Tip: Dream Hotel CEO Chae Hwa Young's
abuse of power)

383
00:25:09,280 --> 00:25:11,310
(Tip: Dream Hotel...)

384
00:25:12,750 --> 00:25:15,420
Dream Hotel CEO Chae Hwa Young's
power abuse scandal.

385
00:25:16,020 --> 00:25:18,760
Proof of Dream Hotel CEO Chae Hwa Young's
ugly true colors.

386
00:25:20,020 --> 00:25:22,590
(Tip: Dream Hotel Chae Hwa Young)

387
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:25,330
(Tip: Dream Hotel Chae Hwa Young)

388
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,400
(CEO Chae Hwa Young: Power Abuse)

389
00:25:26,460 --> 00:25:27,630
(Your email has been sent successfully.)

390
00:25:36,740 --> 00:25:39,180
Baek Ho, I just sent it.

391
00:25:46,820 --> 00:25:48,550
Welcome, Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

392
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:50,820
Hello, Chairman.

393
00:25:51,190 --> 00:25:52,220
Kang Baek Ho?

394
00:25:52,820 --> 00:25:55,460
So that's the lawyer
my Hong Ju is so crazy about.

395
00:25:58,830 --> 00:26:01,160
What's this urgent matter?

396
00:26:01,830 --> 00:26:05,640
Chairman, a friend who's a producer
gave me a scoop.

397
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:06,940
A scoop?

398
00:26:07,940 --> 00:26:11,310
- Is it about Dream?
- Yes.

399
00:26:11,910 --> 00:26:13,240
It's too late
to stop the story from breaking,

400
00:26:13,810 --> 00:26:15,480
so I think our best bet
is a quick response.

401
00:26:16,350 --> 00:26:17,550
That's why I called you, Chairman.

402
00:26:18,420 --> 00:26:19,580
This is urgent, Chairman.

403
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:24,320
CEO Chae abusing her power?

404
00:26:25,890 --> 00:26:29,590
- Is this true?
- As you know, Chairman,

405
00:26:29,890 --> 00:26:34,360
the public is very sensitive to scandals
about the wealthy abusing their power.

406
00:26:34,530 --> 00:26:38,640
So, our quick response
and sincere apology are crucial.

407
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:41,100
Good grief.

408
00:26:41,910 --> 00:26:44,470
CEO Chae, what have you done now?

409
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:54,250
A space that offers the primal joys
and tranquility of nature.

410
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:11,070
What's this? An emergency alert?

411
00:27:11,630 --> 00:27:14,000
Oh my gosh! What in the world is this?

412
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:15,240
What is it?

413
00:27:20,380 --> 00:27:23,210
CEO Chae, we need to do
some damage control right now.

414
00:27:23,550 --> 00:27:24,580
What is it now?

415
00:27:33,490 --> 00:27:39,030
(Breaking News: A Video
of Dream Hotel CEO's Abuse of Power!)

416
00:27:42,870 --> 00:27:44,600
An abuse of power video?
This is ridiculous!

417
00:27:46,040 --> 00:27:47,800
How could this happen?

418
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:54,240
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho. Don't tell me you...

419
00:27:54,810 --> 00:27:56,780
I was just trying to contain the damage.

420
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:04,420
- Father, are you here about the news?
- CEO Chae.

421
00:28:05,060 --> 00:28:08,890
What on earth have you been doing?

422
00:28:44,930 --> 00:28:46,300
(The First Man)

423
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:49,900
CEO Chae's true colors
are finally starting to show.

424
00:28:50,230 --> 00:28:53,200
- You need to issue a public apology.
- You want me to apologize?

425
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:55,370
What the heck do you think you're doing?

426
00:28:55,610 --> 00:28:57,740
You think I don't know
you and your daughter are behind this?

427
00:28:58,040 --> 00:28:59,380
Now you get a taste of your own medicine.

428
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:01,540
- Let go already!
- What do you two think you're doing?

429
00:29:01,980 --> 00:29:06,950
Aren't you Oh Jang Mi?
But my Jang Mi is in the hospital.

430
00:29:07,180 --> 00:29:09,150
Wait, what's Ma Seo Rin doing here?

431
00:29:09,550 --> 00:29:10,550
What, they're twins?

432
00:29:11,220 --> 00:29:13,220
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
